@flexiarg relationship-coherence/capacity-honoring
@title Plan Around the Nervous System, Not Against It
@sigils [🔋/息]
@keywords rest, capacity, depletion, alone-time, disponibilite, nap, boundary, pacing, self-care
@audience correspondents negotiating shared time under real limits
@references [relationship-coherence/low-pressure-bid relationship-coherence/rupture-repair]
@references-extra ["Instance of origin: 2026-04-10 — after fatigue forces a cancelled evening, Joe reframes it forward: 'In future we'll have to figure out how to conduct ourselves so that we get plenty of rest -- that can't be too hard.' Recurs as an explicit institution: Julia's 'disponibilite... is not looking promising' (2026-04-10), 'more alone-time today to recover, is it ok?' (2026-05-19), and mutual 'we should probably spend the night apart' (2026-05-13)."]
@tone practical
@style pattern

! conclusion: Treat each person's depletion as legitimate data and plan the shared time around it — rest, alone-time, and early nights are moves that protect the relationship, not withdrawals from it.

  + context: Two self-directed, over-committed lives (teaching + research + music + jobs, plus therapy days and a dog) meet under chronic tiredness. The relationship's durability turns out to rest on how well it metabolises low-capacity days rather than only high-capacity ones.

  + IF:
    one of you is depleted (illness, overwork, allergy season, the female horrors, a bad night) and the standing plan assumes full capacity.

  + HOWEVER:
    pushing through on empty produces the over-spill it was meant to avoid (see relationship-coherence/rupture-repair); but treating a needed 'no' as a rejection makes rest itself feel like a threat to the bond.

  + THEN:
    name the capacity honestly, ask/offer for the lower-energy version (a quiet day, a night apart, a phone call instead of a visit), and hold it without penalty — 'that makes sense, I am tired too'.

  + BECAUSE:
    the shared world is only as coherent as the two nervous systems sustaining it; protecting rest is protecting the relationship's substrate. A relationship that can run at low power does not have to run at the risk of collapse.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - Pair with relationship-coherence/low-pressure-bid: the graceful out is what lets a capacity-decline be stated at all.
    - Watch the failure twin, martyr-pushing: accepting an invitation past your capacity to spare the other's feelings, which converts fatigue into a rupture later.
